definition.value: An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of both protons from the phosphate group of  ribavirin 5'-monophosphate. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of the three diphosphate OH groups of  ribavirin 5'-diphosphate. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion resulting from the removal of the four triphosphate OH groups of ribavirin 5'-triphosphate. It is the major species at pH 7.3.
A diterpenoid with formula C20H34O2. It is isolated from Penicillium cyclopium and exhibits potent conidiation inducing activity.
A diterpenoid with formula C20H32O2. It is isolated from Penicillium cyclopium and exhibits potent conidiation inducing activity.
An iminium ion resulting from the protonation of the two imine groups of 11-beta-hydroxysaxitoxin; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An iminium ion resulting from the protonation of the two imine groups of beta-saxitoxinol; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An iminium ion resulting from the protonation of the two imine groups of 11-beta-hydroxy-beta-saxitoxinol; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-triphosphate that is ATP carrying an oxo group at position 8.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-triphosphate that is ATP carrying a hydroxy group at position 8.
